<h1 class="sectionheading">About</h1>

<p class="feature">
Anndi Bergset was born and raised in Ohio where her family graciously supported her obsession with museums and fed her appetite for creativity by always keeping the crayon box full and blank paper available. She graduated from Gustavus Adolphus College in St. Peter, Minnesota in 2003 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Art History and followed that three years later, in 2006, with a Master of Fine Arts degree in Theatrical Design from Tulane University in New Orleans, Louisiana. An internship relocated her to the Washington DC metro area where she worked in a production studio and later found full-time work in a fused glass studio and multiple theatres as a set designer and stage prop designer. 
</p>
<p class="feature">
In 2013 she followed her heart to Norway where she now lives with her husband and puppy in a little red house up on a mountain. When Anndi made the big move across the ocean she had more boxes of art supplies and power tools than clothes and now creates from her studio full of windows overlooking the fjord below. In the summer she guides tourists around the Norwegian countryside showing off the glaciers, fjords and mountains. When at home, Anndi enjoys gardening and growing her own vegetables - experimenting with what can be grown at 350 meters above sea level. 
</p>
<p class="feature">
Using all the knowledge she has acquired from formal education and work experiences, she combines techniques to reach across the various creative fields - opening doors to even more creative solutions.
</p>

